title: Jefferies Flags App Store and Google Ad Risks for Apple (AAPL)

title: Apple sued for allegedly breaking US antitrust law, stealing camera tech
summary: Reincubate Ltd, makers of the smartphone video app Camo, has sued Apple for allegedly stealing its patented technology and maintaining an illegal monopoly in the U.S. smartphone software market. The lawsuit claims Apple copied Camo's features into its iOS "Continuity Camera" after actively encouraging Reincubate's development, thereby stifling competition. This action follows a similar antitrust lawsuit filed by the U.S. government against Apple in 2024.

title: Apple’s New AirTag Improves Range, Sound, and Item Sharing
summary: Apple has announced a new AirTag, its first update since 2021, focusing on internal improvements rather than a visual redesign. The updated AirTag features a second-generation Ultra Wideband chip for 50% extended Precision Finding range, a 50% louder speaker with redesigned alerts, and a new "Share Item Location" feature allowing up to five people to track an item. Despite these enhancements, the pricing remains the same at $29 for a single unit and $99 for a four-pack, with orders open since January 26.

title: TotalEnergies signs 10-year green power deal with papermaker SWM
summary: TotalEnergies has signed a 10-year agreement to supply 800 gigawatt-hours of renewable electricity to papermaker SWM at three sites in France. This deal, which commenced this month, is part of TotalEnergies' strategy to expand its integrated power business and helps SWM secure half of its French electricity needs from renewable sources for the next decade, significantly reducing its Scope 1 and 2 emissions. TotalEnergies aims to increase its electricity production by approximately 20% annually, reaching 100 terawatt-hours by 2030, through similar agreements with other major companies.

summary: Zscaler has launched its AI Security Suite to help enterprises manage, secure, and govern their AI usage across various components like development, models, agents, and infrastructure. title: Gartner Predicts by 2028, 50% Of Organizations Will Adopt Zero-Trust Data Governance as Unverified AI-Generated Data Grows
summary: Gartner predicts that by 2028, 50% of organizations will adopt a zero-trust data governance approach due to the increasing volume of unverified AI-generated data. This shift is crucial to safeguard business outcomes and mitigate risks like "model collapse" where AI tools generate inaccurate information. Organizations are advised to appoint AI governance leaders, foster cross-functional collaboration, leverage existing governance policies, and adopt active metadata practices to manage these risks and ensure data integrity.
